com.apple.audio.midi
Class MIDIPacketList

java.lang.Object
  com.apple.audio.CAObject
      com.apple.audio.util.CAMemoryObject
          com.apple.audio.midi.MIDIPacketList
public final class MIDIPacketList
extends CAMemoryObject

Implements the MIDIPacketList as defined in MIDIServices.h. A list of MIDI events being received from, or being sent to one endpoint.

MIDIPacketList

public MIDIPacketList(int dataSize)
Create a new MIDIPacketList, with space for specified bytes of MIDI data that will be packed into MIDIPacket structures. This can be longer than you'll need at any one time, but should be big enough for the maximum amount of data (and its associated headers) that you will expect to add.

Parameters:
dataSize - The number of bytes to be allocated

Prepare a MIDIPacketList to be built up dynamically Note MIDIPacketList is created already prepared to add MIDI data. init allows reuse of a packet list.

CoreAudio::MIDIPacketListInit()

add

public void add(long time,
                MIDIData data)
         throws CAException
Add a MIDI event to a MIDIPacketList. Packet Lists received from a MIDIReadProc are READ ONLY. In that case this call will throw an exception, as the packet list cannot be added too.

CoreAudio::MIDIPacketListAdd()

Parameters:
time - The new event's time.
data - The new event. May be a single MIDI event, or a partial sys-ex event. Running status is not permitted.
